      <h1 class="h1">Nottingham City</h1>
      <h3 class="h3">Accommodation</h3>
      <p>The Street Outreach team (SOT) should always be contacted in the first instance by colleagues or members of the public coming across a rough sleeper on <a href="tel:0800 066 5356">0800 066 5356</a> between 09:00 - 17:00, Monday - Sunday.</p>
      <p><a href="http://www.emmanuelhouse.org.uk/winter-shelter">The Nottingham Night Shelter</a></p>
      <p>The Nottingham Shelter is run by Emmanuel House. Due to the communal nature of this service, it is not running in its usual format, ie. in dormitory style arrangements in church halls, however, there are a limited number of hotel beds available throughout the winter period.</p>
      <h3 class="h3">Access arrangements</h3>
      <p>Those wishing to access the winter shelter will need to be referred through Housing Aid or The Street Outreach team (SOT);
      It is strongly advised that anyone who is rough sleeping contact The Street Outreach Team on their 24 hour freephone telephone number on <a href="tel:0800 066 5356">0800 066 5356</a>.</p>
