      <h2 class="h1 best-practice__header">Procedure for SWEP - out of hours</h2>
      <h3 class="h3">Process for a rough sleeper calling for emergency accommodation between 17:00 - 21:00, Monday to Sunday on a SWEP evening;</h3>
      <p>The individual calls SOT on 0800 066 5356 OR approaches a uniformed officer asking for accommodation;</p>
      <p>SOT/uniformed officer advises the individual to attend the triage service at London Road Fire Station, open from 18:00 - 21:00, Monday to Sunday;</p>
      <p>The individual will be assessed by SOT at the fire station and given hot drink/food by British Red Cross;</p>
      <p>The individual will be given the most appropriate accommodation for their needs;</p>
      <p>Taxi available if the individual has poor mobility;</p>
      <p>SOT will alert Housing Aid;</p>
      <p>Individuals will then be picked up by Housing Aid the following day and referred, where appropriate, to longer term accommodation/reconnected if possible.</p>
      <p>Calls after 21:00 will be dealt with over the phone by SOT. However, every effort will be made to ensure all rough sleepers are offered an option of accommodation before 21:00 during cold weather periods.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
